      <title>Shroud suggestion</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=178719#M178719</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Ghost&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-can do the NPC trick of walking "through" doors (except maybe locked ones that need picklock skill or a key you dont have) BUT&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-cannot aggro or be aggroed by any mob (so can't create trains), cannot loot anything&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-cannot receive flags etc (for quests such as Cartographer Slipgear)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-cannot zone into zones unless teh character has the flag or key for that zone&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Why?&amp;nbsp; Purely for the fun of exploring...I am level 70 so I get to see a lot more now than I used to, but still, sometimes all I see of certain zones is the zone in or some other "safe spot"..only the puller type classes get to see the majority of things in a zone, since fixed duration invis isnt always enough (and constant evaccing is a real bore)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Also, as long as a zone wasn't level restricted to zone in, lower level toons could get to explore some of the non-flag static zones from the expansions, which at least if they can't exp there for a while, they would still get to see some of teh expansions....maybe restrict this shroud's access from teh newest expansion for 2-3 months after launch, so that the "true" explorers (actual players venturing into the zones to exp and raid) get "first dibs"&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Just a suggestion, something purely for the fun factor...ty for your consideration&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
