      <title>Re: Shroud suggestion</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=178922#M178922</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;i'm not sure if it was intentional but I just found it kind of funny that the suggestions above about the 'ghost' form ended up sounding almost exactly like the system they are using in dungeons &amp;amp; dragons online (based on what I saw in public beta and preview event)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In their system when you die you can choose to either respawn at your bind point or wait for 'rez' (their rez is a little different, your groupmates have to take your 'body' to a rez shrine in the dungeon).  If you choose to let your groupmates try to get you rezzed you go into this kind of ghost form.  You can move around while in ghost form...nothing aggros but your vision is 'ghostlike' and makes it a little hard to see.  Your ghost is also leashed to your shard, so if you wander too far from the person carrying your shard you get bounced back to the shard.&lt;br&gt;Its not really that exploitable because of those features, and it would be better to have a groupmate that can actually help you fight instead of a ghost so its not like people would purposely want to die to become ghosts : )&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;So anyway, I think the system is novel and interesting, not quite sure it would be worth the effor to put into EQ -- just thought it really interesting that a few people throwing around ideas in this thread came up with almost the exact same system that DDO did : P&lt;/p&gt;</description>
